14:37.266 --> 14:40.565
- Phil, yeah. Let me call you back in five minutes.
- No, I'm fine.

14:40.636 --> 14:43.628
All right. Thank you.
I'm sorry?

14:43.706 --> 14:46.834
Uh, no, thank you.

14:50.846 --> 14:53.212
Emily really loved
this thing.

14:55.251 --> 14:59.244
We used to keep it
over there on the counter.

15:02.992 --> 15:06.792
Stretch her whole body out
trying to reach it.

15:06.862 --> 15:09.922
Last joint
on her little finger.

15:19.875 --> 15:21.809
What?

15:21.877 --> 15:24.209
N- Nothin'.

15:25.481 --> 15:28.382
Come in.
Sit down, Freddy.

15:38.861 --> 15:41.557
Boy. Tch.

15:41.630 --> 15:46.226
You really look like a natural family.
You could be their father.

15:48.304 --> 15:51.865
Thank you, Freddy.

15:51.941 --> 15:55.570
Spectacular looking family,
really.

15:59.048 --> 16:03.815
Um, what can I, uh,
do for you?

16:06.989 --> 16:09.253
I really came to see Mary.

16:09.325 --> 16:14.991
Oh. Well, I don't mean to be
nosy, Freddy, but what about?

16:15.064 --> 16:18.830
Well, I'd really rather
talk to Mary about that.

16:21.170 --> 16:22.762
Well-

16:24.473 --> 16:26.441
Well, well, well.

16:31.013 --> 16:35.575
- Um, you sure I can't get you something to drink?
- No, I'm fine.

16:38.254 --> 16:40.279
- Anyway, I think they're here.
- Oh, yeah.

16:43.025 --> 16:45.926
Hold on, guys.

16:46.595 --> 16:48.620
Hold on.

16:48.697 --> 16:50.722
- Hi, Dad!
- Hi, guys.

16:50.799 --> 16:53.199
- Hi, Freddy.
- Hi, darling.

16:53.269 --> 16:56.329
- We've got a visitor.
- Come on, Dad.

17:01.477 --> 17:03.445
Well...

17:06.348 --> 17:08.680
look at this.

17:10.586 --> 17:14.488
My own kids
call me Freddy.

17:18.160 --> 17:22.324
- You look wonderful.
- Wonderful, I think, would be pushing it.

17:22.397 --> 17:25.992
No, you do.
You look wonderful.

17:26.902 --> 17:28.836
Thank you.

17:30.372 --> 17:35.207
So, how's business?

17:35.277 --> 17:37.837
So-so.

17:37.913 --> 17:40.711
You know, it's a little jewelry store.
What can I say?

17:40.783 --> 17:43.479
It's business.

17:43.552 --> 17:46.487
What about you?
You still doin' the real estate?

17:46.555 --> 17:49.285
Well, it's a tough market
right now.

17:49.358 --> 17:52.953
I'm still representing
some properties.

17:53.028 --> 17:58.125
But Roger's been doing so well, I've been able
to back off some. Spend more time with the kids.

17:59.235 --> 18:02.170
Oh, well, wonderful.

18:02.238 --> 18:07.175
That's, uh, yeah-
That's, uh, really wonderful.

18:07.243 --> 18:09.939
Um-

18:10.012 --> 18:11.980
Um...

18:13.682 --> 18:16.708
Mary, there's, uh, something
that you should know.

18:16.785 --> 18:21.654
It's the reason
I came here.

18:21.724 --> 18:24.557
- Freddy-
- I've got something I wanna tell you.

18:24.627 --> 18:27.960
You made me a promise.
I hope you're gonna keep it.

18:29.365 --> 18:34.166
Two things:
I made you a promise. That's one.

18:34.236 --> 18:38.696
And I have great news.
That's two.

18:38.774 --> 18:40.833
Now, you gonna let me speak
or not?

18:43.579 --> 18:46.013
I'm sorry.
What's your great news?

18:48.784 --> 18:51.753
It's really great news.
I mean, spectacular news.

18:51.820 --> 18:56.382
- I'm tellin' ya. You wanna
hear it or not? - Mm-hmm.

18:56.458 --> 18:58.858
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

18:58.927 --> 19:00.519
- Are you ready?
- Yes.

19:03.332 --> 19:05.266
He's out.

19:05.334 --> 19:09.270
John Booth is out.

19:09.338 --> 19:11.272
I'm gonna kill him.

19:11.340 --> 19:13.205
Get out of here, Freddy.

19:13.275 --> 19:16.676
I'm not goin' anywhere until I see you
courageous enough to tell the truth.

19:16.745 --> 19:19.270
The truth?
What truth, Freddy?

19:19.348 --> 19:22.010
- You promised you wouldn't.
- Wouldn't? Wouldn't what, Mary?

19:22.084 --> 19:25.349
- Mention our daughter? Why? Because you'd blackmail me?
- Blackmail?

19:25.421 --> 19:28.754
If I ever, ever want to speak
to the mother of my children,

19:28.824 --> 19:30.849
I must never mention
my daughter!

19:30.926 --> 19:34.191
- Get out of our house!
- This is my house.

19:34.263 --> 19:37.596
By any natural law,
this is my house!

19:37.666 --> 19:41.193
If my children live here,
my children,

19:41.270 --> 19:45.263
then who's to say that I can't come here
to see 'em any fuckin' time I want to?

19:45.341 --> 19:48.435
- You had to do it, huh?
- Nobody's talkin' to you!

19:48.510 --> 19:51.104
- You want me to call the police?
- Call whoever the fuck you want.

19:51.180 --> 19:54.343
Where do you get off calling them your children?
You haven't been a father to those kids.

19:54.416 --> 19:57.977
- You stopped with our daughter.
- Emily is her name.

19:58.053 --> 20:01.420
Yes, Emily. Emily!
And she is dead.

20:01.490 --> 20:04.789
But I owe those two little boys
up there all the love I've got.

20:04.860 --> 20:08.694
And it kills you that I can
give it to them and that you can't!

20:11.433 --> 20:14.527
Freddy, I want you
to leave our home-

20:14.603 --> 20:18.039
- Tell the truth, Mary. You want me to kill John Booth!
- Let go of him!

20:18.107 --> 20:22.635
That's my job in life, and your job is
to go on as though nothing happened!

20:22.711 --> 20:25.646
- Let go of him!
- Freddy!

20:25.714 --> 20:29.172
Freddy, why don't you let me go?
I'll make us some coffee.

20:29.251 --> 20:32.049
Come on.

20:32.121 --> 20:35.147
Coffee. Good.

20:35.224 --> 20:37.385
I'd like some coffee.

20:37.459 --> 20:42.419
Why don't we all just sit down, have
some coffee and talk about this civilly?

20:42.498 --> 20:45.262
Come on.

20:45.334 --> 20:48.929
You know what?

20:52.307 --> 20:54.867
I don't want any coffee.
I-

20:57.079 --> 20:59.877
I don't like coffee at all.
It makes my heart-

20:59.948 --> 21:03.247
- You just said you wanted coffee.
- No.

21:03.318 --> 21:05.183
You sure?

21:05.254 --> 21:10.453
Yes. Uh... no.

21:10.526 --> 21:12.756
I'm gonna go.

21:13.862 --> 21:16.922
I feel good.

21:19.902 --> 21:24.862
- He just showed up at the door.
I didn't- - Jesus, God, Roger.

21:24.940 --> 21:27.875
I just want to say this.

21:27.943 --> 21:30.741
I've done a lot of things
for you, you know.

21:30.813 --> 21:33.043
A lot of things.

21:33.115 --> 21:37.575
And I think it's cheap of you that you
won't hear me out on things. I really do.

21:37.653 --> 21:41.089
- Mary's just upset.
- Excuse me, but I am not upset.

21:41.156 --> 21:45.354
If you think I'm gonna keep score on who's
done what to who, you're very fucking wrong!

21:45.427 --> 21:47.918
And if you think that's cheap,
then fuck you!

21:47.996 --> 21:52.228
I don't know if you're serious about
killing this man or not, but I do know this.

21:52.301 --> 21:54.599
It has nothing to do
with our daughter.

21:54.670 --> 21:57.366
Our little girl is gone, Freddy,
and she's not coming back...

21:57.439 --> 22:00.499
no matter what you do!

22:00.576 --> 22:04.603
You've never even been to the cemetery,
Freddy. You've never even been to Emily's grave.

22:04.680 --> 22:06.807
Why?

22:06.882 --> 22:11.649
Because I didn't go to
your little party? Your funeral?

22:11.720 --> 22:15.816
I went on my own time,
Mary... in private.

22:15.891 --> 22:18.485
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

22:18.560 --> 22:22.052
Then you're a braver man
than I thought.

22:22.130 --> 22:24.655
What's the inscription
on the stone, Freddy?

22:26.168 --> 22:28.432
What color is it?

22:28.504 --> 22:31.302
Is it on a hill?
Is it under a tree?

22:31.373 --> 22:34.968
Does it lay flat or does it
stick up out of the ground?

22:41.617 --> 22:44.484
That's what I thought.

22:46.588 --> 22:50.752
Roger, man to man,

22:50.826 --> 22:53.192
when you two read
in the newspaper...

22:53.262 --> 22:56.356
that John Booth
has been shot dead,

22:56.431 --> 23:01.869
I want you to look into her face and
tell me if you don't see pride and relief.

23:01.937 --> 23:05.532
Pride and relief,
Mary.

24:07.402 --> 24:09.370
So, listen to me.

24:09.438 --> 24:11.906
I'm comin' out of the bathroom,
right?

24:11.974 --> 24:14.909
And these two Orientals,
they're arguin', they're hollerin'.

24:14.977 --> 24:17.775
They're screamin'
at one another, and all in Japanese.

24:17.846 --> 24:19.575
So, I told 'em.

24:19.648 --> 24:24.847
I said, "Hey, you're in
America now. Speak Spanish. "

24:27.289 --> 24:31.726
- Geez, you fucking guys.
Have a miserable evening.

24:31.793 --> 24:35.126
What was he doin' in the mens' room?

24:35.197 --> 24:38.792
Hey, Freddy. Freddy.
What?

24:38.867 --> 24:40.801
Hey, Freddy, you with us?

24:40.869 --> 24:44.066
I think we hypnotized him.
Freddy!

24:45.307 --> 24:48.208
- Yeah?
- He's on the rag.

24:51.847 --> 24:56.580
Did any of you guys ever have
a sound build up in your head...

24:56.652 --> 24:59.485
over a period of days?

24:59.554 --> 25:02.079
Like a vacuum cleaner?

25:02.157 --> 25:06.150
That the last time
you had an original thought,

25:06.228 --> 25:09.026
you got cocky
and rode on it?

25:09.097 --> 25:12.624
- Rode what?
- Rode on the thought.

25:13.969 --> 25:16.130
Enjoyed it...

25:17.572 --> 25:22.600
'til you started hearin' that
vacuum cleaner in your brain.

25:22.678 --> 25:27.172
- But you don't mean tonight.
- No. He means some other night.

25:27.249 --> 25:29.945
Take my advice, Freddy.

25:30.018 --> 25:32.919
Get yourself a "youngie" and go
on one of them Laguna weekends.

25:44.833 --> 25:47.529
I gotta take off.
I'll see you guys later.

25:47.602 --> 25:50.366
Freddy, where you goin'?
It's only 11:00.

25:50.439 --> 25:52.202
Oh, man.

25:52.274 --> 25:54.208
Commitments.

25:54.276 --> 25:58.303
He's gonna go turn off the fuckin'
vacuum cleaner!

27:54.996 --> 27:57.521
Pride and relief, Mary.

28:19.054 --> 28:20.988
Goddamn it!

28:21.056 --> 28:23.923
Goddamn it!

28:23.992 --> 28:27.860
Fuckin'-
